atDirectives.description:
Tailwind CSS v4: Defines design tokens (colors, fonts, spacing, etc.) directly in CSS. These tokens are used to generate utility classes.

Example:
```css
@theme {
  --color-brand: #3B82F6;
  --font-sans: 'Inter', sans-serif;
}
```

Tailwind CSS v4: Explicitly tells Tailwind which files to scan for class names when auto-detection is insufficient.

Example:
```css
@source '../node_modules/@my-lib/components';
```

Tailwind CSS v4: Defines a custom utility class that integrates fully with Tailwind (variants, hover, responsive, etc.).

Example:
```css
@utility tab-4 {
  tab-size: 4;
}
```

Tailwind CSS v4: Applies Tailwind variants (like `hover`, `lg`, `dark`) inside arbitrary CSS blocks.

Example:
```css
@variant hover {
  background-color: blue;
}
```

Tailwind CSS v4: Defines a completely new custom variant that can be used like any built-in variant (hover, focus, etc.).

Example:
```css
@custom-variant theme-ocean {
  [data-theme='ocean'] & {
    @slot;
  }
}
```

Tailwind CSS: Inlines any Tailwind utility class directly into your custom CSS rules. Essential for applying Tailwind utilities inside component styles.

Example:
```css
.btn {
  @apply px-4 py-2 rounded-xl font-semibold;
}
```

Tailwind CSS: Groups CSS into one of three layers — `base`, `components`, or `utilities` — to control specificity and order of injection.

Example:
```css
@layer base {
  h1 { @apply text-4xl font-bold; }
}
```

Tailwind CSS v3/v4 compat: Explicitly specifies which Tailwind config file to use for this CSS file.

Example:
```css
@config './tailwind.config.js';
```

Tailwind CSS v4: Loads a Tailwind plugin directly from a CSS file, eliminating the need for a JS config file.

Example:
```css
@plugin '@tailwindcss/typography';
```
